WEBVTT

1
00:01:36.004 --> 00:01:39.304
The mind holds onto painful
memories for a reason...


2
00:01:39.383 --> 00:01:43.104
trying to keep us from making the
same mistakes over and over.


3
00:01:43.178 --> 00:01:45.806
Some say if you go back to where
a painful memory started...


4
00:01:45.889 --> 00:01:51.146
look at the place, walk through it,
you can get free of the hurt and forget.


5
00:01:52.854 --> 00:01:55.357
Maybe I thought that would happen.

6
00:01:55.899 --> 00:01:57.742
I'll tell you though, it would
have been all right with me...


7
00:01:57.818 --> 00:02:00.287
if I never saw this town again.

8
00:02:00.362 --> 00:02:05.539
But it was the only teaching job I could
get, and I needed it, and I took it.


9
00:02:07.327 --> 00:02:09.455
Oh, Jim, it's lovely.

10
00:02:11.039 --> 00:02:13.007
Pretty good, huh?

11
00:02:13.542 --> 00:02:15.215
- Looks boring.
- No.


12
00:02:15.294 --> 00:02:19.674
Oh, come on, you're gonna love it.
It's much better than Chicago.


13
00:02:20.799 --> 00:02:22.722
Of course, things had changed...

14
00:02:22.801 --> 00:02:25.725
but not much, considering
the years that had passed.


15
00:02:25.804 --> 00:02:28.899
No, not nearly enough to keep
my heart from tightening...


16
00:02:28.974 --> 00:02:33.104
to keep me from forgetting that this was
the town where my brother had died.


17
00:02:33.186 --> 00:02:37.316
The same town my parents fled in
fear and grief when I was nine.


18
00:02:37.399 --> 00:02:41.199
The same. Only the
faces had changed.


19
00:02:46.992 --> 00:02:51.122
Sixteen forty-seven, that's
what it said? Are you sure?


20
00:02:51.204 --> 00:02:54.879
- Sixteen forty-seven Harland.
- Okay.


21
00:03:02.049 --> 00:03:06.225
- Hey, where are all the sidewalks?
- That's the least of our problems.


22
00:03:22.611 --> 00:03:24.784
Well, we don't have to stay.
I'll go back to house painting.


23
00:03:24.863 --> 00:03:26.383
I can start with this
shack right here.


24
00:03:26.448 --> 00:03:29.247
No way. You are not a
house painter anymore.


25
00:03:29.326 --> 00:03:31.249
Well, I might not be much of
a teacher either, you know.


26
00:03:31.328 --> 00:03:33.837
Might be a little rusty
after this layoff.


27
00:03:33.863 --> 00:03:36.780
You'll be fine. It's
just like riding a bike.


28
00:03:36.833 --> 00:03:40.588
- You never give up on me, do you?
- Nope. Never.


29
00:03:43.423 --> 00:03:47.929
Okay, two guys with a truck, come on.
Let's unload this van.


30
00:03:49.221 --> 00:03:51.565
Scott could tell that
Sally and I were afraid.


31
00:03:51.640 --> 00:03:54.689
How many years had I worked and
what did we have to show for it?


32
00:03:54.768 --> 00:03:57.612
I wanted to provide for
him, not put him in danger.


33
00:03:57.688 --> 00:03:59.736
- Good night, pumpkin.
- Good night, Mom.


34
00:03:59.815 --> 00:04:01.909
- Sleep well.
- Okay.


35
00:04:03.819 --> 00:04:05.617
- Good night, kiddo.
- Good night, Dad.


36
00:04:05.696 --> 00:04:07.414
Good night.

37
00:04:08.281 --> 00:04:12.912
- What do you think, on or off?
- Off.


38
00:04:12.994 --> 00:04:15.088
- Sure?
- Yeah.


39
00:04:17.124 --> 00:04:19.297
- Good night.
- Good night.


40
00:04:26.508 --> 00:04:30.138
I have a certain way of
breaking in a new house.


41
00:04:35.225 --> 00:04:38.195
I have to establish my territory.

42
00:04:44.401 --> 00:04:46.745
If I had known the
horror we were facing...


43
00:04:46.820 --> 00:04:50.745
I would have taken Sally and Scott in
my arms like my parents took me...


44
00:04:50.824 --> 00:04:53.703
and run from this town forever.

45
00:05:01.668 --> 00:05:04.763
I hear this new teacher threw
some kid out a window in Chicago.


46
00:05:04.838 --> 00:05:08.888
- No, man, he ran him over with his car.
- No, no, that's not what happened.


47
00:05:08.967 --> 00:05:11.345
The guy got fired because
he went berserk in class.


48
00:05:11.428 --> 00:05:13.556
He picked up a chair and threw...

49
00:05:23.565 --> 00:05:26.114
My fifth class today.

50
00:05:26.193 --> 00:05:30.414
I'm a little out of shape.
Thank God you're seniors.


51
00:05:30.489 --> 00:05:32.366
You'll have mercy on me, I hope.

52
00:05:37.454 --> 00:05:41.254
- So I'll do my best to keep you awake.
- We'd rather sleep.


53
00:05:44.711 --> 00:05:48.386
Well, I can tell this is
not love at first sight...


54
00:05:48.465 --> 00:05:51.890
but you got to live with me and
I got to live with you, so...


55
00:05:51.968 --> 00:05:54.517
let's try to enjoy it, okay?

56
00:05:57.891 --> 00:05:59.564
May I?

57
00:06:00.060 --> 00:06:03.109
There's something you should
know about this class.


58
00:06:03.188 --> 00:06:05.782
- Do you have a name?
- Yeah.


59
00:06:06.691 --> 00:06:09.160
- Do you wanna tell it to me?
- Chip Conway.


60
00:06:09.236 --> 00:06:13.161
Or the Chipster depending
on how close you get.


61
00:06:13.949 --> 00:06:17.624
Now, you see, Mr. Jim, sir,
there's a little...


62
00:06:17.702 --> 00:06:20.626
Hold it. It's Mr. Norman
or just Jim.


63
00:06:20.705 --> 00:06:24.926
Yeah, that's what I said.
This isn't a real class.


64
00:06:25.001 --> 00:06:27.299
You see, most of us in here
are on the football team.


65
00:06:27.379 --> 00:06:32.636
It's a special class for jocks
like me and airhead chicks.


66
00:06:33.844 --> 00:06:35.562
Like Kate.

67
00:06:37.472 --> 00:06:40.692
- I'm not an airhead.
- Yeah, right!


68
00:06:40.767 --> 00:06:44.863
Now, let us cruise and we'll
win you a championship.


69
00:06:44.938 --> 00:06:49.159
Pass us and you'll have one
happy squad of killer stompers.


70
00:06:49.234 --> 00:06:51.362
Yeah! Yeah!

71
00:06:51.444 --> 00:06:54.869
You'll pass, if you do the work.

72
00:06:54.948 --> 00:06:57.246
Pass us anyway.

73
00:07:05.375 --> 00:07:09.300
All right, let's just keep it down.
Hold it down. Hey!


74
00:07:10.297 --> 00:07:11.799
Hey!

75
00:07:12.757 --> 00:07:14.384
Shut up!

76
00:07:18.179 --> 00:07:22.184
- Sorry.
- No, really, don't be sorry.


77
00:07:23.143 --> 00:07:26.693
I want to apologize for
the jerks in this class.


78
00:07:26.771 --> 00:07:31.402
- Some of us really wanna learn stuff.
- Thank you... Kate? Thank you.


79
00:07:36.114 --> 00:07:38.788
But I do wanna apologize.

80
00:07:39.534 --> 00:07:43.129
I'm just... I'm a little rusty
at this teaching, and...


81
00:07:43.914 --> 00:07:48.294
- I won't be breaking any more sticks.
- I kind of liked it.


82
00:07:50.921 --> 00:07:54.095
I don't know, Mr. Simmons. This guy's
coming down really hard on us.


83
00:07:54.174 --> 00:07:56.848
- We've got a big responsibility...
- Just a moment.


84
00:07:56.927 --> 00:07:59.646
- Mr. Norman.
- Hello, sir.


85
00:07:59.721 --> 00:08:03.942
- So, how was your first day?
- Well, it was fine, sir. Just fine.


86
00:08:04.017 --> 00:08:08.363
Good. If you have a minute,
I'd like to have a quick chat.


87
00:08:08.438 --> 00:08:11.066
- Sure.
- In my office.


88
00:08:14.653 --> 00:08:16.405
Excuse me.

89
00:08:24.037 --> 00:08:28.964
In 27 years, no one had moved
in after my parents and I left.


90
00:08:29.042 --> 00:08:32.842
What was it about this house
that kept them away?


91
00:08:45.225 --> 00:08:47.478
I'm gonna get you, Jimmy.

92
00:08:55.986 --> 00:08:57.909
Got you now.

93
00:08:58.405 --> 00:09:03.787
No, Wayne. Wayne...
Stop, Wayne! Wayne!


94
00:09:06.621 --> 00:09:09.841
Wayne, no. No, Wayne. Wayne, no.

95
00:09:11.793 --> 00:09:13.545
Wayne!

96
00:09:14.504 --> 00:09:16.723
Run, Jimmy, run!

97
00:09:25.974 --> 00:09:28.397
Sally? Scott?

98
00:09:30.687 --> 00:09:32.781
Surprise!

99
00:09:33.231 --> 00:09:35.905
- Hey, it's enough.
- Look!


100
00:09:36.526 --> 00:09:40.622
- Where did you get this?
- You are married to a very clever woman.


101
00:09:40.697 --> 00:09:44.918
You know, this place really has
potential in a bohemian sort of way.


102
00:09:44.993 --> 00:09:48.839
- We went to the thrift store.
- Don't tell him that, Scott.


103
00:09:48.913 --> 00:09:51.792
I spent a tiny bit of Christmas
money, but it's nice, isn't it?


104
00:09:51.875 --> 00:09:55.425
- It's great.
- And, look, I got this. It's an antique.


105
00:09:55.503 --> 00:09:57.972
Wait a minute,
I'll show you the rest.


106
00:09:58.048 --> 00:10:00.096
I saw the perfect place
downtown today.


107
00:10:00.175 --> 00:10:02.598
Honey, this isn't Chicago.
There is no downtown here.


108
00:10:02.677 --> 00:10:05.396
Well, you know what I mean,
over there in the center of town.


109
00:10:05.472 --> 00:10:07.895
It's a vacant store front.
It's perfect for the shop.


110
00:10:07.974 --> 00:10:09.066
Sounds great.

111
00:10:09.142 --> 00:10:11.645
And I've decided, I'm not
gonna do just flowers.


112
00:10:11.728 --> 00:10:16.074
You know, I think in a place like
this, you can't be so specific.


113
00:10:16.149 --> 00:10:19.699
- Are you okay?
- Yes. I'm all right.


114
00:10:20.320 --> 00:10:23.415
I'm really excited about this place.
I think it's a perfect location.


115
00:10:23.490 --> 00:10:24.992
Can I have my train back?

116
00:10:25.075 --> 00:10:26.952
Yep. Why don't you go get the
mitts and we'll play some ball?


117
00:10:27.035 --> 00:10:29.333
- So how was work?
- It was all right.


118
00:10:29.412 --> 00:10:33.087
The principal called me
into his office today.


119
00:10:33.166 --> 00:10:36.045
Said he didn't want a
Chicago incident here...


120
00:10:36.127 --> 00:10:37.845
that I should watch my anger.

121
00:10:37.921 --> 00:10:40.515
I thought you cleared that
up at the first interview.


122
00:10:40.590 --> 00:10:43.969
Well, I think he just wants
me to know he's watching.


123
00:10:44.052 --> 00:10:49.650
And the students seem to know, too.
I hope the stories don't get out of hand.


124
00:10:50.350 --> 00:10:52.227
Come on, Dad!

125
00:10:52.310 --> 00:10:54.108
Coming! We won't be long.

126
00:10:54.187 --> 00:10:58.317
Yeah, well, don't be long.
Dinner's almost ready.


127
00:11:48.533 --> 00:11:50.080
Sally?

128
00:11:51.077 --> 00:11:52.624
Sally?

129
00:13:04.108 --> 00:13:08.079
You gonna be here for a minute?
You go... Wait a minute.


130
00:13:11.115 --> 00:13:12.833
We're ready.

131
00:13:13.368 --> 00:13:15.621
Yes. Yes.

132
00:13:16.871 --> 00:13:19.340
Does he sing? No.

133
00:13:21.417 --> 00:13:23.715
Does he dance? No.

134
00:13:29.634 --> 00:13:32.638
Oh, honey, stop.

135
00:13:38.726 --> 00:13:40.524
You're awful.

136
00:13:41.938 --> 00:13:43.815
I don't know.

137
00:13:44.857 --> 00:13:46.575
No way.

138
00:14:15.471 --> 00:14:16.347
Jimmy?

139
00:14:19.017 --> 00:14:20.564
Hey.

140
00:14:21.686 --> 00:14:24.940
- Hey, what's eating you?
- Why can't I go to the library with you?


141
00:14:25.023 --> 00:14:26.900
- Who said you can't?
- Mom.


142
00:14:26.983 --> 00:14:30.829
Yeah? Well, I just talked to mom
and I worked everything out.


143
00:14:30.903 --> 00:14:33.247
If you wanna go, you can go,
but you got to carry my books.


144
00:14:33.323 --> 00:14:35.121
Okay-

145
00:14:39.912 --> 00:14:43.712
You and me, Jimmy, we're
always gonna stick together.


146
00:14:45.168 --> 00:14:48.638
I got to pay my library fine,
so I'm gonna need your help.


147
00:14:48.713 --> 00:14:52.388
How much is three
times two, times two?


148
00:14:52.467 --> 00:14:54.561
It's 12.

149
00:14:55.386 --> 00:14:58.060
You're the one who's got
the brains in this family.


150
00:14:58.139 --> 00:15:00.141
Here you go.

151
00:15:15.948 --> 00:15:17.575
Yay!

152
00:15:23.164 --> 00:15:29.217
- We're gonna go through the tunnel?
- Sure. It's faster. Come on.


153
00:15:35.134 --> 00:15:36.681
No!

154
00:15:37.970 --> 00:15:39.597
Wayne!

155
00:15:40.973 --> 00:15:44.853
Don't!

156
00:16:00.493 --> 00:16:03.872
Hey, buttface,
you're blocking the road.


157
00:16:06.707 --> 00:16:11.053
Sissies with books.
Read me a story, sissy.


158
00:16:43.536 --> 00:16:46.255
Do you wanna get through
this tunnel, kid?


159
00:16:46.330 --> 00:16:48.458
You're gonna have to pay.

160
00:16:48.541 --> 00:16:51.340
- We'll go back.
- "We'll go back."


161
00:16:53.421 --> 00:16:56.766
Nope. No other way except our way.

162
00:16:57.467 --> 00:16:59.310
Right, Vinnie?

163
00:17:00.887 --> 00:17:03.231
- So give us some money.
- Leave us alone.


164
00:17:03.306 --> 00:17:07.356
Hey, look, new sneakers.
Let's see if they can fly.


165
00:17:25.077 --> 00:17:27.000
