472
00:51:54.270 --> 00:51:57.270
And they're gonna kill him like they
killed Billy and like they killed Kate.


473
00:51:57.314 --> 00:52:00.659
I know. Okay, sir, I know.
You said that.


474
00:52:01.402 --> 00:52:05.703
You see, well, you seem
to know an awful lot.


475
00:52:05.781 --> 00:52:08.330
A lot of stuff that nobody could
possibly know anything about.


476
00:52:08.409 --> 00:52:11.879
Like finding the girl in the barn.

477
00:52:11.954 --> 00:52:15.800
Like just happening to be on hand
when Billy Stearns was killed.


478
00:52:15.874 --> 00:52:18.718
So you tell me, what
I'm supposed to think?


479
00:52:18.794 --> 00:52:21.013
Look, I don't know what
you're supposed to think.


480
00:52:21.088 --> 00:52:23.307
All I know is my
family is in danger.


481
00:52:23.382 --> 00:52:26.352
- From who? Your students?
- Yes!


482
00:52:26.927 --> 00:52:29.726
God damn it, you charge me
with murder or you let me go!


483
00:52:29.805 --> 00:52:31.682
You sit down!

484
00:52:35.936 --> 00:52:38.655
Does my driving scare you, Chip?

485
00:52:38.731 --> 00:52:42.577
Oh, he's a tough man.
He ain't scared of anything!


486
00:52:50.326 --> 00:52:51.873
Still not scared, huh?

487
00:52:51.952 --> 00:52:54.421
No, no, you're cool as a
corpse, right, Chippie?


488
00:53:01.879 --> 00:53:05.133
Well, boys, what's it gonna
take to scare this guy?


489
00:53:05.215 --> 00:53:09.265
- The face.
- Oh, man, the face?


490
00:53:09.887 --> 00:53:11.514
You do it, North.

491
00:53:12.348 --> 00:53:14.396
That's for kids, man.

492
00:53:15.017 --> 00:53:16.690
I'll do it.

493
00:53:16.769 --> 00:53:19.943
Man, we must be bored
doing this crap.


494
00:53:32.159 --> 00:53:37.211
It ain't working, Vinnie. He ain't scared.
Are you, Chippie, you Knucklehead?


495
00:53:44.838 --> 00:53:46.556
Time to rock, jock.

496
00:54:22.918 --> 00:54:24.670
It's Dad!

497
00:54:29.299 --> 00:54:31.472
Dad, how was jail?

498
00:54:32.553 --> 00:54:36.228
Hey, I wasn't in jail, okay? He just
wanted to ask me some questions.


499
00:54:36.306 --> 00:54:40.152
Scottie, go in and finish your
breakfast. You've got school.


500
00:54:40.811 --> 00:54:42.404
Okay...

501
00:54:47.901 --> 00:54:49.653
They think you killed
Billy and Kate.


502
00:54:49.737 --> 00:54:53.332
- Yeah, but they have no evidence.
- What are you gonna do?


503
00:54:53.407 --> 00:54:55.956
I'm going in to teach. Now,
come on, I want a cup of coffee.


504
00:54:56.034 --> 00:55:00.915
Talk to me, Jim. Why would
they think such a thing?


505
00:55:00.998 --> 00:55:04.673
- Because they're being made to think it.
- By whom?


506
00:55:04.752 --> 00:55:07.255
Please don't shut me out.

507
00:55:07.337 --> 00:55:10.261
We got through your last
breakdown by talking things out.


508
00:55:10.340 --> 00:55:13.560
I don't wanna talk it out,
okay? I'm tired.


509
00:55:13.635 --> 00:55:17.560
I know. You haven't slept for more than
three hours in the last four days.


510
00:55:17.639 --> 00:55:21.109
Look what you're doing to yourself.
I feel as if I'm losing you.


511
00:55:21.185 --> 00:55:24.815
You're not losing me. I just...
I need a little more time, that's all.


512
00:55:24.897 --> 00:55:28.697
I just need some time
to figure this thing out.


513
00:55:47.419 --> 00:55:52.266
It seems another one of your
students did disappear last night.


514
00:55:53.634 --> 00:55:55.352
Chip?

515
00:55:55.427 --> 00:55:59.273
- I told you.
- Yeah. Amazing.


516
00:56:01.058 --> 00:56:04.153
We'll let you know when
we find something.


517
00:56:04.228 --> 00:56:08.699
Or you let us know when
you remember something.


518
00:56:50.858 --> 00:56:55.113
Say, Jimmy, you remember
North here, don't you?


519
00:56:55.195 --> 00:56:57.618
He decided to come up and
visit when Chip cashed in.


520
00:56:57.698 --> 00:57:00.167
Transferred up from Milford.

521
00:57:00.242 --> 00:57:02.665
Now we can finish
unfinished business, Jimmy.


522
00:57:02.744 --> 00:57:06.339
You always wanted to be like
your brother, didn't you, Jimmy?


523
00:57:06.415 --> 00:57:08.884
- Yeah, dead.
- Very dead.


524
00:57:09.835 --> 00:57:12.714
- You can't run away this time.
- Tonight's the big night, Jimmy.


525
00:57:12.796 --> 00:57:14.798
Don't tell us you don't remember
today's the anniversary?


526
00:57:14.882 --> 00:57:17.931
He probably forgets his wife's.

527
00:57:18.010 --> 00:57:23.062
And speaking of family, how's
that kid of yours, Jimmy?


528
00:57:23.140 --> 00:57:24.983
Bet he's a chicken.

529
00:57:27.352 --> 00:57:30.652
- Just like his old man.
- We'll find out.


530
00:57:31.815 --> 00:57:34.113
See you tonight, Jimmy boy.

531
00:57:34.735 --> 00:57:37.409
Be there or be square, man.

532
00:57:42.993 --> 00:57:45.121
Leave my family out of this!

533
00:57:45.203 --> 00:57:48.503
- Hey, man, what are you doing?
- Come on, don't hurt us.


534
00:57:48.582 --> 00:57:50.676
Hey, be cool, man.

535
00:58:04.514 --> 00:58:08.360
And after that level, you turn
into a rocket. It's really cool.


536
00:58:08.435 --> 00:58:11.234
Well, anyways, see you guys later.

537
00:58:50.644 --> 00:58:54.774
Mommy, help me! Please, help me!
Somebody help!


538
00:58:54.856 --> 00:58:57.985
Help! Please! Help me!

539
00:59:11.790 --> 00:59:13.383
What happened?

540
00:59:13.458 --> 00:59:15.552
Thank God, he's okay.

541
00:59:15.627 --> 00:59:18.881
Some guys in a black
car tried to hit him.


542
00:59:18.964 --> 00:59:20.762
The cops are out looking for them.

543
00:59:20.841 --> 00:59:24.471
- Did anybody else see the car?
- No, just Scotty.


544
00:59:26.388 --> 00:59:30.894
Well, we'll get you inside.
Let's get you cleaned up.


545
00:59:37.941 --> 00:59:41.787
Now you don't have to sleep.
I just want you to rest. Okay?


546
00:59:45.657 --> 00:59:47.455
Dad?

547
00:59:48.577 --> 00:59:50.796
Can we leave here?

548
00:59:55.333 --> 00:59:59.179
It won't happen again,
Scotty. I promise you.


549
00:59:59.254 --> 01:00:02.633
We're all gonna be fine. Okay?

550
01:00:03.800 --> 01:00:09.227
You know, I have been saving something
for you and I wanted you to have it.


551
01:00:09.306 --> 01:00:12.185
I've just been waiting
for the perfect time.


552
01:00:12.267 --> 01:00:15.737
This was given to me
when I was your age.


553
01:00:16.855 --> 01:00:20.576
And it means a lot to me.
I want you to have it.


554
01:00:23.111 --> 01:00:25.034
Thanks, Dad.

555
01:00:27.449 --> 01:00:29.326
It's cool.

556
01:00:34.081 --> 01:00:35.754
Looking good.

557
01:00:47.260 --> 01:00:48.807
Sally?

558
01:00:52.682 --> 01:00:54.355
Honey?

559
01:00:59.231 --> 01:01:00.904
Sally?

560
01:01:03.235 --> 01:01:04.782
Sally?

561
01:01:05.570 --> 01:01:08.915
- Didn't you hear me?
- The dryer was on.


562
01:01:14.704 --> 01:01:16.251
You got to listen to me.

563
01:01:16.331 --> 01:01:19.505
There are some punks in my
class and they're after me.


564
01:01:19.584 --> 01:01:22.053
They are the ones that
tried to scare Scotty.


565
01:01:22.129 --> 01:01:24.973
That's what this is about.
They're killers.


566
01:01:25.048 --> 01:01:29.519
They killed Billy, they killed
Kate and now they want me.


567
01:01:30.846 --> 01:01:34.567
Why would kids in your
class wanna kill you?


568
01:01:36.434 --> 01:01:39.734
They're the same guys
that killed my brother.


569
01:01:42.107 --> 01:01:45.031
Jim, how do you expect
me to respond to that?


570
01:01:45.110 --> 01:01:47.704
The boys who killed
your brother are dead.


571
01:01:47.779 --> 01:01:52.660
They were killed by a train. You know
that. How could they be alive?


572
01:01:52.742 --> 01:01:54.119
They're not.

573
01:01:54.202 --> 01:01:59.299
Twenty-seven years ago, today, they killed
Wayne and now they came back for me.


574
01:01:59.374 --> 01:02:03.095
They told me, they're gonna play
this whole thing out again.


575
01:02:03.170 --> 01:02:05.593
Look, I am not crazy.

576
01:02:05.672 --> 01:02:07.891
You got to believe me.

577
01:02:08.675 --> 01:02:13.306
I want you to lock all the doors and
windows and don't let anybody in.


578
01:02:29.279 --> 01:02:30.656
Jimmy?

579
01:02:30.739 --> 01:02:32.537
What's wrong?

580
01:02:41.708 --> 01:02:45.554
Excuse me. I need to find a policeman
from about 20, 25 years ago.


581
01:02:45.629 --> 01:02:48.758
- His name was Nell. Officer Nell.
- That'd be Bob Nell.


582
01:02:48.840 --> 01:02:51.093
Right. I got to see him.
It's very, very important.


583
01:02:51.176 --> 01:02:53.645
No, he hasn't been on
the force in years.


584
01:02:53.720 --> 01:02:55.973
He got shot during a burglary
call some years ago.


585
01:02:56.056 --> 01:02:57.683
Almost died, poor bastard.

586
01:02:57.766 --> 01:02:59.985
He's over in Smithfield now,
the retirement home.


587
01:03:00.060 --> 01:03:03.064
I got to warn you, he's
gone around the bend a bit.


588
01:03:03.146 --> 01:03:07.026
Ever since his accident,
he thinks he sees dead people.


589
01:03:12.656 --> 01:03:13.999
Jimmy?

590
01:03:14.699 --> 01:03:18.670
- Jimmy Norman!
- My God, you remember me.


591
01:03:18.745 --> 01:03:23.876
You look into a person's eyes,
you always know who he is or was.


592
01:03:24.751 --> 01:03:27.095
I've been waiting for you, son.

593
01:03:32.092 --> 01:03:36.563
Hey, slow it down.
This is a residential area.


594
01:03:38.556 --> 01:03:40.979
Jimmy and Wayne Norman.

595
01:03:41.059 --> 01:03:44.609
- You two were something else.
- Yes, sir, we were.


596
01:03:46.815 --> 01:03:49.694
I know this is gonna
sound crazy, but...


597
01:03:50.485 --> 01:03:54.661
those boys, the ones
who killed Wayne...


598
01:03:57.284 --> 01:03:59.912
I think they're back again.

599
01:03:59.995 --> 01:04:02.043
I know. I saw him.

600
01:04:02.122 --> 01:04:05.877
- You saw who?
- Your brother Wayne.


601
01:04:06.751 --> 01:04:09.470
He needs you to settle it.

602
01:04:09.546 --> 01:04:10.593
Wayne?

603
01:04:13.008 --> 01:04:16.103
There was this routine burglary.

604
01:04:16.720 --> 01:04:19.690
Routine except that
I got shot in the head.


605
01:04:19.764 --> 01:04:23.689
The doctors said I was clinically
dead for over three minutes.


606
01:04:23.768 --> 01:04:28.114
And that's when I saw him,
Wayne, from the other side.


607
01:04:28.189 --> 01:04:32.160
He was waiting,
stuck in that midrealm.


608
01:04:33.028 --> 01:04:37.499
That dimension between here
and one's final destination.


609
01:04:38.742 --> 01:04:42.121
Sometimes, son,
they're in our hearts.


610
01:04:42.203 --> 01:04:45.332
Sometimes they're in our thoughts.

611
01:04:45.415 --> 01:04:50.012
But if they're unhappy enough,
if something's left unsettled...


612
01:04:50.920 --> 01:04:52.888
sometimes they come back.

613
01:04:55.884 --> 01:04:57.557
They...

614
01:04:57.635 --> 01:05:03.859
Those punks told me they had
transferred in from Milford.


615
01:05:04.809 --> 01:05:07.858
I checked. I can't
find any Milford High.


616
01:05:10.023 --> 01:05:12.902
That's because it isn't a school.

617
01:05:42.680 --> 01:05:43.681
Lawson.

618
01:05:50.605 --> 01:05:52.278
North.

619
01:05:54.776 --> 01:05:56.494
Vincent.

620
01:05:58.238 --> 01:06:02.869
- Hey, Mueller! Mueller!
- You coward.


621
01:06:03.493 --> 01:06:05.587
Mueller...

622
01:06:07.330 --> 01:06:08.752
Yes...

623
01:06:14.087 --> 01:06:18.137
- Welcome to Milford, Jimmy.
- Looking for Mueller, kid?


624
01:06:18.216 --> 01:06:22.062
You're gonna need him
to put this all together.


625
01:06:22.137 --> 01:06:26.483
- Unless we find him first.
- So you better get going, Daddy-O.


626
01:06:26.558 --> 01:06:29.152
You don't have much time.

627
01:06:30.603 --> 01:06:34.608
You're going down tonight, Jimmy!
Tonight, Jimmy!


628
01:07:14.105 --> 01:07:16.483
I'm looking for Karl Mueller.

629
01:07:16.566 --> 01:07:18.239
Who are you?

630
01:07:19.277 --> 01:07:23.157
Jimmy Norman. Wayne
Norman's little brother.


631
01:07:27.702 --> 01:07:29.830
What do you want?

632
01:07:31.581 --> 01:07:33.800
Boy, look at you.

633
01:07:33.875 --> 01:07:36.219
You're the man who punched
my big brother...


634
01:07:36.294 --> 01:07:40.094
knocked him down on the ground and
kicked him when he was defenseless, huh?


635
01:07:40.173 --> 01:07:43.393
Is this what happens to
tough guys like you, huh?


636
01:07:47.388 --> 01:07:50.107
That thing with your
brother was an accident!


637
01:07:50.183 --> 01:07:54.108
Hell, I almost got killed myself.
I just got out right before the train hit.


638
01:07:54.187 --> 01:07:58.533
- Come on, you're coming with me.
- Hey, where are you taking me, man?


639
01:08:00.401 --> 01:08:01.994
Let's go!

640
01:08:03.112 --> 01:08:05.114
Come on, get out!

641
01:08:06.407 --> 01:08:10.503
- What is this? What are we doing here?
- Reliving your past.


642
01:08:10.578 --> 01:08:11.579
Come on!

643
01:08:11.663 --> 01:08:13.791
Mueller, don't you know?
Your buddies are back.


644
01:08:13.873 --> 01:08:16.342
Lawson, Vinnie, North!

645
01:08:16.417 --> 01:08:19.341
For every life they took,
one of them came back.


646
01:08:19.420 --> 01:08:22.469
Seems they're here to finish up some old
business and we're part of the plan.


647
01:08:22.549 --> 01:08:25.098
- You're crazy!
- Yeah?


648
01:08:25.176 --> 01:08:28.976
All right, I'm here with Mueller!

649
01:08:29.055 --> 01:08:31.399
I'm waiting for you!

650
01:08:31.474 --> 01:08:34.603
This is freaking crazy. You're nuts!
I'm getting out of here.


651
01:08:34.686 --> 01:08:39.066
Mueller, come back here!
You coward!


652
01:12:00.558 --> 01:12:04.062
Hello, Mrs. Norman. Can
Jimmy come out and play?


653
01:12:27.543 --> 01:12:30.296
Welcome to the
neighborhood, Mrs. Norman.


654
01:12:35.718 --> 01:12:37.846
Hello, baby!

655
01:13:05.414 --> 01:13:07.792
Nice shooting, Jimbo.

656
01:13:09.460 --> 01:13:12.430
But you can't kill
what's already dead.


657
01:13:15.424 --> 01:13:18.598
All right, come on. Come on,
I'm not running this time.


658
01:13:18.678 --> 01:13:20.055
Good, then we'll see you there.

659
01:13:20.137 --> 01:13:22.231
We wanted to make sure
you were coming, Jimmy.


660
01:13:22.306 --> 01:13:26.186
Bring the wife and kid.
It's fun for the whole family.


661
01:13:32.108 --> 01:13:33.405
Come on, let's go.

662
01:13:33.484 --> 01:13:36.363
- Where are we gonna go?
- Someplace safe.


663
01:13:42.493 --> 01:13:44.336
Come on, come on!

664
01:13:45.288 --> 01:13:47.382
Get inside, come on!

665
01:13:59.427 --> 01:14:03.057
Come on now. You and Scotty
will be safe in here.


666
01:14:03.139 --> 01:14:05.312
My brother promised me.

667
01:14:07.059 --> 01:14:08.777
They were the ones who
killed him, weren't they?


668
01:14:08.853 --> 01:14:13.279
Yeah. And my students.

669
01:14:14.150 --> 01:14:16.369
Why are they after you?

670
01:14:26.203 --> 01:14:27.705
Hey, kid!

671
01:14:28.706 --> 01:14:32.336
- They want revenge.
- For what?


672
01:14:33.127 --> 01:14:36.131
- Something that happened on that day.
- Oh, let's just go.


673
01:14:36.213 --> 01:14:38.341
We could just get in the
car and never come back.


674
01:14:38.424 --> 01:14:41.644
No, they'll find me. They'll
follow me no matter where I go.


675
01:14:41.719 --> 01:14:43.721
I can't keep running.

676
01:14:44.597 --> 01:14:49.774
I have to change what happened,
and then after tonight it'll all be over.


677
01:14:51.187 --> 01:14:52.780
Jim?

678
01:14:54.273 --> 01:14:56.947
I'm so sorry that I doubted you.

679
01:14:57.610 --> 01:14:59.408
I love you.

680
01:15:07.495 --> 01:15:09.497
I will come back.

681
01:17:10.493 --> 01:17:13.417
So you were the one who took them.

682
01:17:21.170 --> 01:17:23.889
What are you doing here, Mueller?

683
01:17:26.342 --> 01:17:29.061
I've been coming by
this place for years.


684
01:17:29.136 --> 01:17:33.812
I used to park my car across the street
at night and just look at the place.


685
01:17:35.518 --> 01:17:38.863
I watched it fall apart,
just like me.


686
01:17:38.938 --> 01:17:41.532
I never meant anything to
happen to your brother.


687
01:17:41.607 --> 01:17:46.454
You got to believe me. My life's
been hell since that clay.


688
01:17:48.864 --> 01:17:52.164
I know it's crazy,
but I believe what you say.


689
01:17:53.661 --> 01:17:55.914
I believe they're back.

690
01:17:56.580 --> 01:18:00.676
I guess somehow I always
knew they would be.


691
01:18:06.006 --> 01:18:10.352
- So what do you wanna do?
- I'm tired of being afraid.


692
01:18:12.972 --> 01:18:15.725
I'm not gonna be afraid anymore.

693
01:18:18.894 --> 01:18:20.896
Let's do it.

694
01:18:57.308 --> 01:19:00.027
You know, I bet Vinnie
here a whole nickel...


695
01:19:00.102 --> 01:19:03.322
that your old clunker
wouldn't burn rubber, Jimmy.


696
01:19:03.397 --> 01:19:05.491
But I was wrong.

697
01:19:05.566 --> 01:19:07.739
Everything burns.

698
01:19:07.818 --> 01:19:11.448
What do you know?
It's Mueller time.


699
01:19:11.530 --> 01:19:13.157
Is that you, Mueller?

700
01:19:13.240 --> 01:19:15.834
What are you doing, man?
You belong with us, remember?


701
01:19:15.910 --> 01:19:19.540
Look at you. You used
to be cool, man.


702
01:19:19.622 --> 01:19:21.875
- Until your little belly turned yellow.
- My God!


703
01:19:21.957 --> 01:19:23.504
- You got old.
- And ugly.


704
01:19:23.584 --> 01:19:25.552
You stink, but we
missed you, Mueller.


705
01:19:25.628 --> 01:19:29.553
You're gonna stand with us,
just like old times, man.


706
01:19:32.509 --> 01:19:36.855
The gang's all here.
Everybody except for Wayne.


707
01:19:38.265 --> 01:19:40.563
He's a definite no-show.

708
01:19:50.986 --> 01:19:54.365
No! No!

709
01:20:01.872 --> 01:20:04.250
- So, where we going?
- You don't know?


710
01:20:04.333 --> 01:20:06.006
He sure as hell does.

711
01:20:06.085 --> 01:20:08.838
We're going to the tunnel
for old times' sake, Mueller.


712
01:20:08.921 --> 01:20:12.266
But first, I thought we'd stop off at
the old church to see some friends.


713
01:20:21.934 --> 01:20:23.436
Mom?

714
01:20:24.645 --> 01:20:29.242
- I'm hungry.
- Soon, when your father gets back.


715
01:20:31.360 --> 01:20:33.283
It's Dad!

716
01:20:33.362 --> 01:20:34.488
Scotty!

717
01:20:35.406 --> 01:20:38.956
- Scotty, no.
- Did you light a candle for me?


718
01:20:39.034 --> 01:20:41.628
- What are you waiting for?
- Go ahead.


719
01:20:41.704 --> 01:20:44.002
Yeah, you first, Einstein.

720
01:20:53.882 --> 01:20:59.264
Light a candle for me, Sally!
Come on out here, pretty baby!


721
01:21:22.619 --> 01:21:26.214
Oh, please, Wayne. 
Please, help me.

722
01:21:27.374 --> 01:21:31.595
I need you. I can't
do this by myself.


723
01:21:33.714 --> 01:21:36.763
No matter what the pain
or the cost, I'll pay it.


724
01:21:36.842 --> 01:21:39.436
Please, please, help me!

725
01:22:28.602 --> 01:22:31.822
Wayne! Please!

726
01:22:34.858 --> 01:22:37.156
Please, help me!

727
01:22:37.778 --> 01:22:40.156
Did you feel that?

728
01:22:40.239 --> 01:22:41.912
Yup.

729
01:22:41.990 --> 01:22:45.085
I thought I felt someone
trying to come through.


730
01:22:45.160 --> 01:22:49.506
Hey, Mueller,
maybe it was your mama.


731
01:22:50.332 --> 01:22:53.176
Maybe it was your mama, North!

732
01:22:54.586 --> 01:22:55.508
Sally?

733
01:22:57.005 --> 01:23:01.602
We're gonna come back when we're
welcome, baby, around midnight.


734
01:23:03.303 --> 01:23:05.055
Come on, Mueller.

735
01:23:23.365 --> 01:23:25.834
- Scott?
- Dad's here!


736
01:23:28.454 --> 01:23:30.172
Scott!

737
01:23:31.999 --> 01:23:34.502
You love your daddy, Scott?

738
01:23:36.336 --> 01:23:39.316
It's a nice kid you
got here, Mrs. Norman.


739
01:23:39.342 --> 01:23:42.459
If you hurt him,
I swear to God, I'll...


740
01:23:42.509 --> 01:23:45.513
Hey, come on, don't hurt the kid!

741
01:23:45.596 --> 01:23:47.940
Shut up, Mueller.

742
01:24:00.277 --> 01:24:04.953
Don't you know, Sally, that
nobody hits me and lives?


743
01:24:05.574 --> 01:24:07.952
You're lucky I have a
date tonight to keep.


744
01:24:08.035 --> 01:24:11.960
Otherwise you and I might have
a little fun of our own! Huh?


745
01:24:13.707 --> 01:24:16.301
It's time to wail, boys.

746
01:24:25.969 --> 01:24:29.519
"How much is three
times two, times two?"


747
01:24:30.224 --> 01:24:33.774
"Oh, that's easy, 12."

748
01:24:35.562 --> 01:24:41.160
"Like I always said, Jimmy, you got
all the brains in the family."


749
01:24:44.863 --> 01:24:47.958
"You're not gonna go through
the tunnel, are you?"


750
01:24:48.033 --> 01:24:50.912
"Sure. It's faster."

751
01:25:12.307 --> 01:25:15.902
Hey, buttface,
you're blocking the road.


752
01:25:15.978 --> 01:25:18.572
Oh, sissy with books.

753
01:25:18.647 --> 01:25:20.820
Read me a story, sissy?

754
01:25:20.899 --> 01:25:22.401
Dad! Dad, help!

755
01:25:22.484 --> 01:25:24.486
- Scotty?
- Dad, help!


756
01:25:24.570 --> 01:25:26.664
Call it insurance, Jimmy.

757
01:25:26.738 --> 01:25:30.663
We wanted to make sure you weren't
gonna chicken out on us this time.


758
01:25:39.126 --> 01:25:40.503
Jim!

759
01:25:40.586 --> 01:25:42.179
Dad!

760
01:25:42.254 --> 01:25:43.676
Jim!

761
01:25:55.100 --> 01:25:59.856
Well, well, well, it's
good to see you, Jimmy.


762
01:25:59.938 --> 01:26:02.282
You know the routine.

763
01:26:02.357 --> 01:26:04.359
- How much money have you got?
- Twelve cents.


764
01:26:04.443 --> 01:26:07.447
Liar. You gonna run and tell on us?

765
01:26:11.700 --> 01:26:13.953
- I'm not running anywhere.
- Good.


766
01:26:14.036 --> 01:26:18.416
'Cause we're gonna finish it this time.
And you're gonna come with us.


767
01:26:20.876 --> 01:26:24.346
Wayne, I know you're
with me. I can feel you.


768
01:26:29.760 --> 01:26:31.683
What's going on?

769
01:26:31.762 --> 01:26:36.438
This. You wanna get through this
tunnel, you gotta pay, get it?


770
01:26:37.309 --> 01:26:39.607
- So how much money have you got?
- Jim!


771
01:26:39.686 --> 01:26:42.280
I told you, 12 cents.

772
01:26:43.398 --> 01:26:46.652
- Mueller, what the hell are you doing?
- Leave him alone.


773
01:26:46.735 --> 01:26:50.239
Vinnie, get this bum out
before I smack him!


774
01:26:57.746 --> 01:27:00.795
What are you doing? You're
not supposed to kill him!


775
01:27:00.874 --> 01:27:04.219
- You're gonna mess the whole thing up!
- Shut up!


776
01:27:04.294 --> 01:27:06.547
He deserved it!

777
01:27:07.589 --> 01:27:12.766
For every life they take,
another can come back, right?


778
01:27:26.566 --> 01:27:28.534
We're gonna have company, boys.

779
01:27:53.301 --> 01:27:54.803
My God!

780
01:27:58.348 --> 01:28:00.350
Wayne?

781
01:28:00.434 --> 01:28:02.186
Now the gang's all here, Vinnie.

782
01:28:02.269 --> 01:28:04.897
- Leave us alone.
- Shut up!


783
01:28:06.148 --> 01:28:07.741
Shut up.

784
01:28:07.816 --> 01:28:10.057
You wanna get through this
tunnel, you gotta pay, get it?


785
01:28:10.110 --> 01:28:13.239
- We're not going back!
- No!


786
01:28:13.321 --> 01:28:15.540
There ain't no other way
back except our way!


787
01:28:15.615 --> 01:28:18.368
I said, leave us alone.

788
01:28:33.508 --> 01:28:36.432
You ain't coming
back this time, kid!


789
01:28:38.263 --> 01:28:40.357
Vinnie, heads up!

790
01:28:45.187 --> 01:28:48.817
Man, nobody hits me.

791
01:28:54.029 --> 01:28:55.781
Oh, my God.

792
01:28:55.864 --> 01:28:57.707
There's no train running
through here anymore.


793
01:28:57.783 --> 01:29:02.004
- Run, Jimmy, run!
- Lawson? Remember this?


794
01:29:04.247 --> 01:29:06.500
This is why you died.

795
01:29:21.932 --> 01:29:22.899
No way.

796
01:29:28.897 --> 01:29:31.696
It's all over, Lawson.
Now you can go to hell!


797
01:29:31.775 --> 01:29:35.951
- Next time, man, there's always next time.
- No, this is it.


798
01:29:36.029 --> 01:29:38.407
Come on. Let's go!

799
01:29:41.326 --> 01:29:42.373
Come on.

800
01:29:47.290 --> 01:29:48.883
Come on. Come on. Run for it.

801
01:29:48.959 --> 01:29:50.552
Go!

802
01:29:50.627 --> 01:29:53.380
- Come on, come on.
- No!


803
01:29:57.467 --> 01:30:01.472
- Come on! Come on!
- Hey, kid!


804
01:30:06.560 --> 01:30:08.312
Get down!

805
01:30:39.175 --> 01:30:40.768
Dad!

806
01:30:43.138 --> 01:30:46.483
- You all right?
- Yeah, I'm okay.


807
01:30:47.684 --> 01:30:49.186
Okay-

808
01:30:51.146 --> 01:30:52.819
Jimmy?

809
01:30:54.566 --> 01:30:59.072
- No, Jim's my dad.
- But that's my cap. I gave it to Jimmy.


810
01:30:59.154 --> 01:31:00.906
I know you did.

811
01:31:01.781 --> 01:31:04.785
And I gave it to my son.

812
01:31:04.868 --> 01:31:08.213
His name is Scott.
He's named after our dad.


813
01:31:09.998 --> 01:31:13.252
I'm your brother, Wayne. I'm Jimmy.

814
01:31:15.003 --> 01:31:19.008
No, that can't be.
Jimmy's my little brother.


815
01:31:23.553 --> 01:31:26.033
- I'm still your little brother.
- My brother's nine years old.


816
01:31:26.056 --> 01:31:27.808
I grew up.

817
01:31:28.683 --> 01:31:31.061
It's been 27 years since...

818
01:31:34.606 --> 01:31:36.825
Since you died.

819
01:31:46.826 --> 01:31:50.922
I don't wanna go back.
Please, I wanna stay.


820
01:31:50.997 --> 01:31:55.548
- I was all alone there.
- I'd do anything to have you back again...


821
01:31:55.627 --> 01:31:58.722
to make up for all
those lost years.


822
01:32:01.007 --> 01:32:03.135
You can't stay.

823
01:32:04.427 --> 01:32:06.771
Then come with me, Jimmy.

824
01:32:12.227 --> 01:32:15.231
Please, Jimmy, 
I need you with me.

825
01:32:15.981 --> 01:32:19.360
We were always gonna stick
together, remember?


826
01:32:20.860 --> 01:32:24.865
Wayne, please try to understand.

827
01:32:25.907 --> 01:32:28.160
I can't go with you.

828
01:32:29.744 --> 01:32:36.252
I have a wife and a son and
I love them very much.


829
01:32:36.334 --> 01:32:38.086
Wayne?

830
01:32:38.920 --> 01:32:41.469
Jim loves you so much.

831
01:32:42.215 --> 01:32:44.809
But we need him here.

832
01:32:44.884 --> 01:32:47.182
Scotty needs him.

833
01:32:47.679 --> 01:32:50.683
The same way that Jimmy needed you.

834
01:32:51.725 --> 01:32:56.151
I can't go with you, Wayne.
But you won't be alone anymore.


835
01:32:57.063 --> 01:33:01.443
Now that this is over, you're
gonna go to a better place...


836
01:33:01.526 --> 01:33:04.325
where Mom and Dad
are waiting for you.


837
01:33:05.155 --> 01:33:07.123
I love you, Wayne.

838
01:33:08.533 --> 01:33:13.755
And you'll always be in my
heart and in my thoughts.


839
01:33:15.540 --> 01:33:21.013
And one day, we'll be
together again, I promise.


840
01:33:39.856 --> 01:33:41.574
Wayne?

841
01:33:43.443 --> 01:33:47.573
You and me, we'll
always stick together.


842
01:34:23.358 --> 01:34:29.536
Scotty, I want you to hold on
to these and don't lose them.


843
01:34:30.490 --> 01:34:32.618
What are they?

844
01:34:32.700 --> 01:34:34.873
Good luck coins.

845
01:34:34.953 --> 01:34:37.547
My big brother gave them to me.